OL,3,CPopular man killed in a 'split second'
OL,4,Cin single punch attack
OL,6,FThe family of a man who died in a
OL,7,Fsingle punch attack say that despite
OL,8,Ftheir "horrendous" loss they feel
OL,9,Fsorry for his killer.
OL,11,FScott Hendy sustained a critical head
OL,12,Finjury when he was punched by George
OL,13,FBaylis outside a pub in Pilning on 2
OL,14,FMarch. The 46-year-old died the next
OL,15,Fday.
OL,17,FBaylis admitted manslaughter and has
OL,18,Fnow been jailed for four and a half
OL,19,Fyears.
